`<space>` toggle selection -> maybe `<tab>` as well?

`in[v]ert` - reverse selection

`[u]mark` - unselect all

copy, cut, and paste like vim ydp

`[c]lear` - unark copy/cut

`:` - lf commands
`$` - shell commands
`%` - shell-pipe (input of command into the lf ui)
`!` - shell command, but 'press-any-key to continue' (e.g. `find -name *.go`)
`&` - async commands
`/?` - `nN`  search like vim (with as usual)
`z` - menu: toggle items; change values
`s` - sort by / info options
`e` - edit
`i` - pager
`w`  - shell

no built in multiplexer : use a server in the background
  e.g. copy paste sticks between instances!

